history.content:
I have Rao right now for 70 and I think he is alright, but not the best lecturer.  He kind of mumbles, but I do like his slides; they go well with the course notes.

Babak is a good professor, and he is into education.  He goes over details thoroughly, although he tries to apply education research, so he little things like random breaks, and he likes to have students answer questions in lecture.  Overall his lectures are good.

Can't speak for Ramchandran, but I hear is very popular for EE 126, so he should be very good.

-----------

children.subject: Deciding between 61B in the fall with Hilfinger vs 70 in the fall with Ramchandran (would take the other one over summer). What would you recommend? I'm really confused. I'm in L&S and I think I'll end up with a B+ in 61A :(
Ramchandran is amazing. He is very clear and concise, and does a great job answering questions. I'd say Ramchandran and Shewchuk are my two favorite teachers by far.
Unrelated, but I would highly recommend Prof. Babak. He is an amazing lecturer. No exxageration. I had him for EE 16A. He knows how to explain topics very well from first principles.
